tData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmNTIzNDhmNi0yMzA0LTQxNWUtYjE2Yy0xZmIyNTI3OTQwNjYiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnZpZGlhLmNvbS9lbi11cy9nZWZvcmNlL3J0eC1yZW1peC8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUzNzBmN2EwLTQ1YWUtNDk3OC05MGYwLTRjMWYwMjQ4ZWQwNSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAViQyTO3vfQnki1DMSoXmWXyU0-x-yaEBNCxSt7OngIC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-us%2Fgeforce%2Frtx-remix%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid"><ins>RTX Remix 创建工具包完成的，这与原始版本的精神保持一致。</ins></a> NVIDIA 还聘请了著名的改装者来实现资产现代化并改善照明。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>对于外行来说， <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.moddb.com/mods/portal-prelude"><em>《传送门：序曲》</em></a>最初于 2008 年发布，由模组制作者开发。它是原版游戏的前传，背景设定在 GLaDOS 之前。该游戏提供了一个长达 10 小时的战役，其中有近 20 个测试室、一个完全配音的故事和超越第一个<em>Portal 的机制。</em>它仍然是评价最高的 Portal 模组，并且不乏竞争。</p><p>这次重制花费了八个月的开发时间，并作为上述改装工具包 RTX Remix 的展示。 <em>Portal: Prelude</em>现已在 Steam 上提供，只要您拥有原始<em>Portal，就无需花费任何费用，</em>所以请下载吧。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/nvidia-drops-remake-of-fan-favorite-mod-portal-prelude-on-steam-for-free-130050799.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nvidia-drops-remake-of-fan-favorite-mod-portal-prelude-on-steam-for-free-130050799.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5370f7a0-45ae-4978-90f0-4c1f0248ed05</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jul 2023 13:00:50 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689620721</ingested><modified> 2023-07-17T19:05:26+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="500" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/6ed3b920-24d4-11ee-bffb-b6599bbf307f" width="800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="500" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/6ed3b920-24d4-11ee-bffb-b6599bbf307f" width="800"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Portal: Prelude]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Image of 'Portal: Prelude']]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Portal: Prelude]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Canon EOS R50 review: Big performance for a tiny camera]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>佳能无反光镜 EOS R 无反光镜相机系列目前已有 11 名成员，但迄今为止大多数都是价格超过 1,000 美元的高端型号。不过，最近该公司一直在吸引精打细算的消费者，推出了<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-eos-r100-is-canons-cheapest-r-series-mirrorless-camera-yet-084049616.html">480 美元的 R100</a>和本次评测的主题——680 美元、24 兆像素<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATDtRg9e27a9MwKjHF-uZugc8xbnjDdNztaS4Y5SDupU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCanon-Mirrorless-RF-S18-45mm-Smartphone-Connection%2Fdp%2FB0BTTV6CT1" class="rapid-with-clickid">R50 等</a>型号。</p><p> R50 使用来自<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/canon-eos-r10-mirrorless-camera-review-180003395.html">980 美元的 EOS R10</a>的 24 兆像素 APS-C 传感器，因此图像质量应该不相上下。否则，您可以将 R50 视为旧版<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/canons-eos-m-50-mark-ii-mirrorless-camera-is-aimed-at-creators-093954801.html">M 接口 M50 Mark II</a>的 RF 接口版本，但具有未裁剪 4K 等更新，使其更适合创作者。同时，它更轻更小，因此非常适合旅行、街头摄影等。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="55fdca9fb7994d9994f6d7c10ae8b5c0" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>售价 480 美元的 R100 瞄准的是低端无反光镜市场，而售价 680 美元的 R50 瞄准的是对摄影和内容创作更认真的用户。它有足够的理由来吸引这些用户吗？让我们来看看。</p><h3>车身与操控</h3><div id="f8dd7826f608444da97d90b993f66149"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2Rzrf2nhSnA?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen scrolling="no"></iframe></div><h3></h3><p> EOS R50 的重量和尺寸都很小，含电池和存储卡的重量仅为 375 克。凭借类似的轻小型镜头，如 18-45mm 套件或新的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdIN8JCaWDgU_ovNKuwr1db_kXc5C6YXQgW_DYP_x0mD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCanon-RF28mm-Wide-Angle-Full-Frame-Cameras%2Fdp%2FB0C66JMX91%2Fref%3Dsr_1_2" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Canon-RF28mm-Wide-Angle-Full-Frame-Cameras/dp/B0C66JMX91/ref=sr_1_2?crid=1QPK3A1AXBH4B&amp;keywords=RF+28mm&amp;qid=1688986981&amp;sprefix=rf+28mm%2Caps%2C239&amp;sr=8-2&amp;ufe=app_do%3Aamzn1.fos.c3015c4a-46bb-44b9-81a4-dc28e6d374b3" class="rapid-with-clickid">28mm 煎饼型号</a>，它可以轻松放入小包中。旅行者和游客通常会选择智能手机，而不是随身携带笨重的相机，但 R50 消除了这一障碍。</p><p>然而，在可用性方面需要付出一定的代价。它的握把相对较小，实际上无法与大镜头一起使用，尽管它确实有很好的橡胶材料，因此它不会从你的手中滑落。</p><p>与其他车型相比，R50 的操控也有所欠缺。它只有一个转盘来更改设置，这意味着您必须按下曝光补偿按钮才能在手动模式下在快门速度和光圈之间切换。但由于该相机是为习惯智能手机的初学者设计的，因此它本质上是设计为通过触摸屏控制的。效果很好，但主菜单项有点小而且繁琐。</p><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="b690312c-6970-4d6b-8331-165e1ff4354c" /><p> 2.95 英寸的触摸屏很不错，具有相对较高的 160 万点分辨率。与所有其他佳能 EOS R 相机一样，它具有完全的铰接功能，非常适合自拍和视频博客。但电子取景器处于低端，相对较小，分辨率较低，为 236 万点。</p><p>它使用与 EOS R10 相同的小电池，一次充电只能拍摄 370 张照片——这也许是该相机最大的弱点。然而，与原始 M50 II 的 305 张照片相比，这是一个显着的改进。其他功能包括一个麦克风但没有耳机端口、一个慢速 UHS-I 卡插槽、USB-C 和微型 HDMI 端口，是的，还有一个非常适合其目标市场的内置闪光灯。</p><h3>表现</h3><p>面向预算的相机的一个重大问题是缺乏良好的自动对焦系统——这对于相机新手来说至关重要。幸运的是，R50 的混合相位检测自动对焦非常稳定。它是 R3 等高端相机自动对焦的简化版本，能够顽强地跟踪拍摄对象并捕捉清晰的照片。</p><p>它可以追踪眼睛、面部和头部，以及包括狗、猫、鸟和马在内的动物。它还跟踪赛车、自行车、火车和飞机等车辆。您可以让系统选择主题，也可以点击触摸屏自行选择。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5c228cd0-2181-11ee-96ee-0dc1db762817" style="height:1238px;width:2200px;" alt="佳能 EOS R50 评测：小相机的强大性能" data-uuid="bd14f096-9778-31da-b4d5-59b6522a9740"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">史蒂夫·登特 (Steve Dent)</div></figure><p>与人类相比，动物和车辆的性能不太可靠。如果您距离拍摄对象太远，拍摄对象跟踪通常会丢失拍摄对象。但总的来说，人工智能系统是可靠的，尤其是对人类来说。</p><p>这非常适合连拍，对于这么小的相机来说，连拍速度快得惊人。它可以在机械快门模式下以高达 12 fps 的速度抓取帧，在静音电子模式下以高达 15 fps 的速度抓取帧。然而，由于缓冲区较小且存储卡插槽速度较慢，您一次只能连拍 42 个 JPEG 图像，并且只能存储 7 个未压缩的 RAW。</p><p>除了通常的手动和自动拍摄模式之外，R50 还为初学者提供了创造性的设置，包括称为 A+ 高级自动的设置。如果它检测到由于高对比度或黑暗而难以拍摄的场景，它会拍摄四张照片并将它们组合成一张 JPEG 图像，就像智能​​手机多年来所做的那样。结果可能令人愉悦，但也可能看起来处理过度。</p><p>正如您所期望的那样，它没有内置稳定功能，因此您需要依靠光学稳定镜头来实现这一点 - 而 APS-C 系列中只有两款镜头。它们只能提供 4 档减震效果，但足以实现 1/10 秒左右的锐利拍摄。使用静音快门功能时，请注意会出现一些卷帘快门效果，但其控制得相当好。</p><h3>画面质量</h3><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="eeb6f50e-3b3a-4bbe-9ac4-f1573349b230" /><p>由于 R50 与 R10 共用 24 兆像素传感器，因此照片质量几乎相同。对于正常拍摄，我看到了色彩准确的照片，肤色偏暖，这是佳能色彩科学的典型特征。 JPEG 在锐化和降噪之间取得了良好的平衡，而 RAW 文件则提供了相当大的空间来调整图像。</p><p>不过，低光性能并不令人惊叹。 ISO 6400 几乎是一个硬性限制，即使这样，你也没有足够的空间来增强黑色而不产生大量噪音。而且你没有体内稳定功能来帮助低快门速度。</p><p>幸运的是，R50 确实有一个内置闪光灯，可以在光线不足时进行补充。只需确保在设置中调低照明级别，以避免拍摄对象过曝。 </p><section data-eng-breakout="84188f4178f54d1aa38850398c75f4dc" data-eng-breakout-type="e2ehero"><img class="e2ehero-url" src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/c70f5ca0-217f-11ee-8895-5058fc70c54e" style="height:1467px;width:2200px;" alt="佳能 EOS R50 评测：小相机的强大性能"></section><h3>视频</h3><p>EOS R10 提供裁剪后的 4K 60p 视频，而 R50 仅限于 4K 30p。幸运的是，它是未裁剪的，并且是从 6K 进行超级采样的。慢动作的分辨率仅限于 1080p，但幸运的是它可以拍摄高达 120fps 的帧率，尽管 60fps 的清晰度要高得多。</p><p>它是迄今为止市场上最便宜的相机，通过 HDR PQ 模式提供 10 位模式，但正常使用时需要对镜头进行一些调整。可能会提高动态范围的 C-Log 模式尚不可用，但对于其目标细分市场来说并不是真正必要的。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5c4e57c0-2181-11ee-adfe-b066e19c6b5b" style="height:1238px;width:2200px;" alt="佳能 EOS R50 评测：小相机的强大性能" data-uuid="bae98cc9-1eb3-336f-b119-b27a2ace2ec6"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">史蒂夫·登特 (Steve Dent)</div></figure><p>对于相对较小且便宜的相机来说，R50 提供了出色的视频质量。过采样的视频非常清晰，色彩准确且人性化。 4K 视频不被裁剪这一事实对于视频博主来说是一个巨大的优势。</p><p>对于这个价位的相机来说，自动对焦也很出色，顽强的跟踪能力在大多数情况下都能保持焦点清晰。它还具有“特写演示模式”，其工作原理与索尼的产品展示模式非常相似，可以快速将焦点从您的脸部切换到您带到相机前的任何物体。</p><p>只要您尝试平稳移动，数字稳定功能就可以用于行走和说话。所有这些使 R50 成为视频博主和内容创作者准备超越智能手机的出色相机。</p><h3>包起来</h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5c23c550-2181-11ee-a09d-4af91c24c959" style="height:1238px;width:2200px;" alt="佳能 EOS R50 评测：小相机的强大性能" data-uuid="2e4697e9-a248-3478-a10f-754315fc3477"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">史蒂夫·登特 (Steve Dent)</div></figure><p>凭借 R50，佳能在性能和经济性之间找到了良好的平衡。 R10 在 980 美元的较高价位上有很多竞争者，而 680 美元的 R50 只有少数竞争对手</p><p>它的主要竞争对手是<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-expands-its-vlogging-lineup-with-the-zv-e-10-mirrorless-camera-142731045.html">索尼售价 700 美元的 ZV-E10</a> ，它在视频博客方面稍好一些，但在摄影方面则不太好。另一种选择是<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nikons-lightweight-z-30-mirrorless-aps-c-camera-targets-content-creators-093725302.html">700 美元的尼康 Z30</a> ，它提供类似的功能集，但缺乏 EVF，并且自动对焦不太可靠。</p><p>如果这些型号太多了，佳能刚刚发布了 480 美元的 R100，这是市场上最便宜的新型无反光镜相机。内容创作者可能会倾向于索尼 ZV-E10，但如果您正在寻找一款功能齐全的混合相机，佳能 R50 是一个不错的选择。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/canon-eos-r50-camera-review-123006238.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/canon-eos-r50-camera-review-123006238.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 3993ca4d-e97e-4a8a-9779-127debfdd67a</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jul 2023 12:30:06 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689687848</ingested><modified> 2023-07-18T13:44:18+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cameras & Photography]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1389" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/f8daf6b0-21b9-11ee-beff-cb536c723b8c" width="2400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1389" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/f8daf6b0-21b9-11ee-beff-cb536c723b8c" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Steve Dent for Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Canon EOS R50 review: Big performance for a tiny camera]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Canon EOS R50 review: Big performance for a tiny camera]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Neopets is fixing its flash games and working on a social life-sim mobile app]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Neopets 团队对曾经备受喜爱的虚拟宠物网站制定了<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/17/23798368/neopets-relaunch-website-flash-games">宏伟的计划</a>，希望它最终能够跟上时代的步伐。在<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://medium.com/@neopetsofficial/a-new-era-for-neopets-fdb5c9ac187e">Medium 上发表的一篇长文</a>中，该团队宣布新的 Neopets 网站将于 7 月 20 日上线。它仍将位于<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://neopets.com/">相同的 URL</a>上，但它将包含该品牌的所有公告以及所有不同游戏和产品的链接。改造背后的人员目前正在尝试解决错误和移动浏览器兼容性问题。他们还在探索使用 Ruffle（一个 Flash 播放器模拟器）来让旧的基于 Flash 的 Neopets 游戏再次可以玩。</p><p>拥有《尼奥宠物》的公司计划根据曾经深受喜爱的虚拟宠物网站<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-11-neopets-tv-show.html">制作一部动画节目</a>，但在关闭之前未能发布该系列节目。 Neopets 团队在其公告中透露，他们已经有了新的领导层，并已为其未来项目筹集了超过 400 万美元的资金。团队成员显然对品牌的未来持乐观态度。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>事实上，该团队并不打算停止改进网站。显然，它已决定转向移动应用程序，并从头开始构建一款名为<em>“尼奥宠物世界”的</em>社交生活模拟游戏。目前，计划是从尼奥宠物的角度开发一款游戏。玩家将能够装饰自己的家园、探索 3D 土地并与朋友一起玩迷你游戏，类似于<em>《动物森友会》</em>等游戏。不过，听起来该项目仍处于早期阶段，是否会实现还有待观察。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/neopets-is-fixing-its-flash-games-and-working-on-a-social-life-sim-mobile-app-121509727.html ?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/neopets-is-fixing-its-flash-games-and-working-on-a-social-life-sim-mobile-app-121509727.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8975d9dd-873a-404f-8ca9-bd396efed9e2</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jul 2023 12:15:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689681730</ingested><modified> 2023-07-18T12:02:14+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Small Businesses]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="1035" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/94c8f180-255c-11ee-baef-fa6dfcfc273a" width="1600"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1035" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/94c8f180-255c-11ee-baef-fa6dfcfc273a" width="1600"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Neopets]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A laptop and a phone showing the new Neopets website.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Neopets]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The US government wants to label secure IoT devices with a 'Cyber Trust Mark']]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> As our homes continue to get smarter, so does the need for additional precautions across devices. Now, the federal government is taking steps to make it easier for you to know the safety of certain devices. The Biden-Harris administration has announced the &quot; <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/statements-releases/2023/07/18/biden-harris-administration-announces-cybersecurity-labeling-program-for-smart-devices-to-protect-american-consumers/">US Cyber Trust Mark&quot; program</a> , which would certify and label Internet of Things (such as baby monitors and alarm systems) with powerful cybersecurity.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-12-05-jfk-assassination-bullets-national-archives.html">National Institute of Standards and Technology</a> (NIST) will determine the necessary cybersecurity qualifications for consumer-grade routers by the end of 2023. Bad actors can manipulate consumer-grade routers without strong security in place for eavesdropping and cyber attacks on other devices. Its criteria will determine if a product should be labeled and certified, using factors like incident detection capabilities and strong default passwords. At the same time, the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ford-secures-92-billion-loan-from-us-department-of-energy-to-build-ev-battery-factories-102520341.html">US Department of Energy</a> is working with National Labs, among other partners, to determine the best path forward to classify smart meters and power inverters as meeting cybersecurity requirements.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) is filing for a national trademark to put on all certified items, and it plans to create a QR code that links to a database of products. &quot;We knew that we didn&#39;t want to create a label that said this product had been certified and secured and then stayed secure forever,&quot; a White House official told reporters. &quot;The QR code will give you up-to-date information on the ongoing adherence to cyber security standards.&quot; Companies such as <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/logitech-acquires-streaming-console-maker-loupedeck-081558711.html">Logitech</a> , Best Buy, <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsungs-viewfinity-s9-5k-display-will-cost-1599-when-it-arrives-in-august-093926336.html">Samsung Electronics</a> and Amazon have expressed their support and intentions to improve cybersecurity in their product offerings.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/the-us-government-wants-to-label-secure-iot-devices-with-a-cyber-trust-mark-114551964.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-us-government-wants-to-label-secure-iot-devices-with-a-cyber-trust-mark-114551964.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> cb949e27-78b6-4ed6-9de9-0c469e718480</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jul 2023 11:45:51 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689679446</ingested><modified> 2023-07-18T11:24:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="533" medium="image" url="https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/54351059925426108adb33b1b2f533fd" width="800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="533" medium="image" url="https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/54351059925426108adb33b1b2f533fd" width="800"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE PHOTO - U.S. President Biden and Vice President Harris attend a meeting at the White House]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Biden takes aim at &#39;excess&#39; oil profits, denounces Pelosi attack]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best GPS running watches for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Because I&#39;m the editor of Engadget by day and a volunteer coach in my free time, I often get asked which GPS watch or fitness tracker to buy. (People also ask what I&#39;m wearing and the answer is: All of them. I am testing all of them.) For my part, the best running watches are quick to lock in a GPS signal, offer accurate distance and pace tracking, last a long time on a charge, are comfortable to wear and easy to use.</p><p> Advanced tracking features like monitoring VO2 Max, or maximum oxygen intake during workouts with increasing intensity, are also nice to have, along with training assessments to keep your workload in check and make sure you&#39;re getting in effective aerobic and anaerobic workouts. It&#39;s also a plus when a watch supports other sports, like cycling and swimming, which all of these do to varying extents. As for features like smartphone notifications and NFC payments, they&#39;re not necessary for most people, especially considering they drive up the asking price.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Without further ado, I bring you capsule reviews of four running watches, each of which I ultimately recommend, none of which is perfect. And keep in mind, when it comes time to make a decision of your own, there are no wrong answers here: I like Apple and Garmin enough, for instance, that I switch back and forth between them in my own training.</p><h2> Best GPS running watches</h2><h2> The best running watch that&#39;s also a smartwatch: Apple Watch </h2><p><core-commerce id="94a533b0a2e54bc3a7e7415624c6a40d" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Stylish design; a great all-around smartwatch you&#39;ll want to use even when you&#39;re not exercising; automatic workout detection; heart-rate and blood oxygen monitoring; support for lots of third-party health platforms; auto-pause feels faster than on Garmin watches; zippy performance and fast re-charging; optional LTE is nice to have.</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> For iPhone users only; shorter battery life than the competition might concern endurance athletes; fewer performance metrics and settings than what you&#39;d find on a purpose-built sports watch.</p><p> Don&#39;t think of <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJESE00OUJKL3JlZj1mc19hX3d0Ml91czI_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1pZy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNWRhYTUwMGMtMzE0Ny0zZGM5LThmNWUtZDUwOGZhMTQwODczIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAToraXkDYFKj-9PFJffEwa7b2dXTT668LWG07ldGLb84&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BDHM49BJ%2Fref%3Dfs_a_wt2_us2%3Fth%3D1">the Apple Watch</a> as a running watch. Think of it as a smartwatch that happens to have a running mode. Almost eight years after the original Watch made its debut, Apple has successfully transformed its wearable from an overpriced curiosity to an actually useful companion device for the masses. But being a gadget for the masses means that when it comes to running, the Apple Watch has never been as feature rich as competing devices built specifically for that purpose.</p><p> Before I get to that, a few words on why I like it. The <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-series-8-real-world-test-130031046.html">Apple Watch</a> is the only one of these watches I&#39;d want to wear every day. (And I do: After reviewing Apple Watches for years, <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/what-we-bought-our-favorite-gadgets-of-2021-irl-140052965.html">I finally purchased one</a> in fall 2021.) The most recent model is stylish, or at least as stylish as a wrist-based computer can be, and certainly more so than any running watch I&#39;ve encountered. The aluminum, water-resistant body and neutral Sport band go with most outfits and will continue to look fresh after all your sweaty workouts and jaunts through the rain. And the always-on display is easy to read in direct sunlight.</p><p> The battery life is 18 hours, according to Apple. Indeed, I never have a problem making it through the day. I&#39;m often able to put the watch back on after a night of forgetting to charge it and still have some juice left. If you do forget, even a few minutes of charging in the morning can go a long way, even more so now that the Watch supports even faster charging than before. Plus, the <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N1cHBvcnQuYXBwbGUuY29tL2VuLXVzL0hUMjEzMzM2IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1ZGFhNTAwYy0zMTQ3LTNkYzktOGY1ZS1kNTA4ZmExNDA4NzMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAWoa1BRKRvxq3ycGetv7OGtXY74YRp7b9sMdiaKEbpid&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fen-us%2FHT213336">new low power mode</a> in watchOS 9 can help you extend the life of your Watch on particularly long days.</p><p> That said, it&#39;s worth noting that other running watches claim longer usage time — between 30 and 40 hours in some cases. When it comes to workouts specifically, Apple rates the battery life with GPS at up to seven hours. Given that, I would trust the Watch to last through a short run or even a half marathon, but I&#39;m not sure how it would fare in one of my slow, five-hour-plus marathons. We haven&#39;t put the higher-end <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-ultra-review-battery-life-compass-gps-hike-130055477.html">Apple Watch Ultra</a> through such paces yet, but it&#39;s worth mentioning that it has the longest battery life of any Apple Watch with a promised 36 hours (and we got about three days worth of regular use during our testing).</p><p> The built-in activity tracking app is simple and addictive: I feel motivated to fill in my &quot;move&quot; (active calorie), exercise and stand rings each day. I enjoy earning award badges, even though they mean nothing. I&#39;m grateful that the Apple Health app can pull in workouts from Garmin and every other brand featured here, and then count that toward my daily exercise and stand goals (but not my move goal, curiously).</p><p> My one complaint is that the sensors don&#39;t always track standing time accurately. I have failed to receive credit when standing for long periods in front of a stove, but occasionally I&#39;ve been rewarded for doing absolutely nothing.</p><p> As for running specifically, you&#39;re getting the basics and not much else. You can see your distance, calorie burn, heart rate readings, average pace and also rolling pace, which is your pace over the past mile at any given moment. You can also set pace alerts — a warning that you&#39;re going faster than you meant to, for example. Like earlier Apple Watches, you can also stream music or podcasts, if you have the cellular-enabled LTE model.</p><p> Because the watch has a GPS sensor, you can leave your phone at home while running. Of course, no two brands of running watches will offer exactly the same distance readout on a run. That said, though Apple never explicitly claimed the Watch offers improved accurate distance tracking, the readouts here do feel more accurate than on earlier models. It&#39;s possible that Apple is making ongoing improvements under the hood that have added up to more accurate tracking performance.</p><p> For indoor runners, the Apple watch integrates with some treadmills and other exercise equipment, thanks to a two-way pairing process that essentially trades notes between the device and gym gear, formulating a more accurate estimate of your distance and effort using that shared data. In my experience, the Watch usually agrees with the treadmill on how far I ran, which is not always the case with other wearables.</p><p> I also particularly appreciate that the Apple Watch automatically detects workouts after a certain period of time. I use this feature daily as I walk to and from the subway and around my neighborhood. After 10 minutes, the familiar vibrating tick, with a message asking if I want to record an outdoor walk. The answer is always yes, and the watch thankfully includes the previous 10 minutes in which I forgot to initiate a workout.</p><p> Regardless of the workout type, all of your stats are listed on a series of pages, which you swipe through from left to right. In my early days using the watch, it was tempting to use the Digital Crown as a stopwatch button, similar to how I use other running watches. This urge has mostly subsided as I&#39;ve gotten more comfortable with the user interface.</p><p> Like many of its competitors, the Apple Watch has an auto-pause option, which I often use in start-and-stop workouts. I also found in side-by-side comparisons (one watch on each wrist), that auto-pause on the Watch reacts faster than on Garmin models.</p><p> Conveniently, the Apple Watch can export workouts to MyFitnessPal so you get credit for your calorie burn there. Of note, the Watch has all of the health features that the previous generation, including a built-in ECG test for cardiac arrhythmias, along with fall detection, a blood oxygen test, respiratory tracking, emergency calls and menstrual tracking. Also like previous models, there&#39;s a built-in compass and international emergency calling.</p><p> Unfortunately, the stats themselves are fairly limited, without much room for customization. There&#39;s no mode for interval workouts, either by time or distance. There&#39;s also not much of an attempt to quantify your level of fitness, your progress or the strenuousness of your workouts or training load. None of this should be a dealbreaker for more casual runners.</p><p> For more detailed tracking, your best bet is to experiment with third-party running apps for the iPhone, like Strava, RunKeeper, MapMyRun, Nike Run Club and others. It&#39;s through trial and error that I finally found an app with Watch support and timed intervals. But at the end of the day, it&#39;s easier to wear a purpose-built running watch when I&#39;m running outdoors, sync my data to Apple Health, get my exercise and standing-time credit, and then put the Apple Watch back on the first chance I get. But if you can only afford one smartwatch for training and life, there&#39;s a strong case for choosing this one.</p><h2> The best for triathletes: Garmin Forerunner 745 </h2><p><core-commerce id="f5a3c4ead4e046d7beb9aee8230bf41c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Accurate distance tracking; long battery life; advanced fitness and training feedback; stores up to 500 songs; works with Garmin Pay.</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Garmin&#39;s auto-pause feature feels slower than Apple&#39;s; more advanced features can sometimes mean the on-device UI is tricky to navigate; features like Garmin Pay drive up the price but may feel superfluous.</p><p> If the Apple Watch is for people who want a smartwatch that also has some workout features, the $500 <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9HYXJtaW4tRm9yZXJ1bm5lci1Fc3NlbnRpYWwtU21hcnR3YXRjaC0wMTAtMDI0NDUtMDAvZHAvQjA4RzU4NVhZSi8_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1pZy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNWRhYTUwMGMtMzE0Ny0zZGM5LThmNWUtZDUwOGZhMTQwODczIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAW41yNXs-eDtxB16qsjEKkp4UW92GtIFe4nCrG7KNNHG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGarmin-Forerunner-Essential-Smartwatch-010-02445-00%2Fdp%2FB08G585XYJ%2F%3Fth%3D1&amp;uuid=CXL7gLO4V547tfth15967">Garmin Forerunner 745</a> is for athletes in training who want a purpose-built device to help prepare for triathlons. The various sensors inside can track your heart rate zones, VO2 Max and blood oxygen (with the option to track all-day and in-sleep, as opposed to just spot checking). On the software side, you get daily workout suggestions, a rating that summarizes your performance condition, animated on screen workouts, a cycling power rating, a sleep score and menstruation tracking. You can also create round-trip courses as well as find popular routes though Garmin&#39;s Trendline populating routing feature.</p><p> Like other Garmin watches, even the entry-level ones, you also get feedback on your training load and training status (unproductive, maintaining, productive, peaking, overreaching, detraining and recovery), a “Body Battery” energy rating, recommended recovery time, plus Garmin Coach and a race time predictor. And you can analyze “running dynamics” if you also have a compatible accessory.</p><p> The slight downside to having all of these features is that the settings menu can be trickier to navigate than on a simpler device like the entry-level <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWbQoANzRUpXw8zlWMgoO21jqGprV9AaPIyvstFZ5cIv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGarmin-Forerunner-Running-Training-Support%2Fdp%2FB07R2YWVW8%3Fth%3D1">Forerunner 45</a> . Fortunately, at least, a home screen update released back in fall 2020 makes it so that you can see more data points on the 1.2-inch screen with less scrolling required.</p><p> Speaking of the screen, the watch face, available in four colors, is easy to read in direct sunlight, and weighs a not-too-heavy 47g. That light weight, combined with the soft silicone band, makes it comfortable to wear for long stretches. Garmin rates the battery life at up to seven days, or up to 16 hours with GPS in use. (That figure drops to six hours when you combine GPS tracking with music playback.) In my testing, I was still at 88 percent after three hours of GPS usage. Most of my weekday runs are around 35 minutes and that, it turns out, only puts a roughly two- or three-percent dent in the battery capacity.</p><p> In practice, the watch also seemed quicker than my older <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-07-11-garmin-forerunner-645-music-review.html">Forerunner 645 Music</a> to latch onto a GPS signal, even in notoriously difficult spots with trees and cover from tall buildings. As always, distance tracking is accurate, especially if you start out with a locked-in signal, which you always should. Like I said earlier, though, I did find in a side-by-side test, Garmin&#39;s auto-pause feature seems sluggish compared to Apple&#39;s.</p><p> Aside from some advanced running and cycling features, what makes the 745 one of the more expensive models in Garmin&#39;s line are its smartwatch features. That includes Garmin Pay, the company&#39;s contactless payments system, and music storage for up to 500 tracks on the device. You can also mirror your smartphone notifications and use calendar and weather widgets. Just know you can enjoy that even on Garmin&#39;s entry-level model (more on that below).</p><p> I can see there being two schools of thought here: if someone plans to wear this watch for many hours a week working out, it may as well get as close as possible to a less sporty smartwatch. Then there&#39;s my thinking: You&#39;re probably better off stepping down to a model that&#39;s nearly as capable on the fitness front, but that doesn&#39;t pretend as hard to be a proper smartwatch.</p><p> For those people, there&#39;s another mid-range model in Garmin&#39;s Forerunner line that&#39;s cheaper and serves many of the same people who will be looking at the 745. The <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9HYXJtaW4tRm9yZXJ1bm5lci1TbWFydHdhdGNoLUFkdmFuY2VkLUR5bmFtaWNzL2RwL0IwN1FMVkhCTEY_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8taWctMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjVkYWE1MDBjLTMxNDctM2RjOS04ZjVlLWQ1MDhmYTE0MDg3MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAbVna9x8TOUf_LWCj2u6aGMehk8ST7zDy5TjZypP6gHa&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGarmin-Forerunner-Smartwatch-Advanced-Dynamics%2Fdp%2FB07QLVHBLF">Forerunner 245</a> offers many of the same training features. It also mostly matches the 745 on pool swimming, but you do appear to lose a bunch of cycling features, so you might want to pore over <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1;pdid:this comparison chart" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUpLJ6e7jUumWDs3kfhu2I2bao6aRkHFQmgqbhFEOrKU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fbuy.garmin.com%2Fen-US%2FUS%2Fcatalog%2Fproduct%2FcompareResult.ep%3FcompareProduct%3D698632%26compareProduct%3D713363%26compareProduct%3D646690%26compareProduct%3D741137" data-demonetize-referrer="https://fave.co/3JvnTtB" class="rapid-with-clickid">this comparison chart</a> before buying if you&#39;re a multisport athlete.</p><p> What you give is Garmin Pay; the option of all-day blood oxygen tracking; the sleep score; a gyroscope and barometric altimeter; floors climbed; heat and altitude acclimation; yoga and pilates workouts; training load focus; the Trendline feature; round-trip course creation, Garmin and Strava live segments; and lactate threshold tracking (and for this you would need an additional accessory amway).</p><p> At the opposite end of the spectrum (for people who actually wish the 745 could do more), there&#39;s the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQbb9QcgVQlza6tA3JuLgHL-vmc1kr3CK1Ba5n4JOr6o&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FForerunner-Multisport-Smartwatch-Connectivity-Wearable4U%2Fdp%2FB096WH8J9M%2F">Forerunner 945 LTE</a> which, true to its name, adds built-in LTE connectivity. This model also holds 1,000 songs, up from 500 on the 745, and adds niceties like preloaded maps and a host of golfing features, if golf is also your jam.</p><h2> The best for most people: Garmin Forerunner 45S </h2><p><core-commerce id="6e5fd63a7e1b4f7cb2099fcac60ab3aa" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Accurate distance tracking, long battery life, heart rate monitoring and interval training at a reasonable price; lightweight design; offered in a variety of colors; smartphone notifications feel limited, but could be better than nothing.</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Garmin&#39;s auto-pause feature feels slower than Apple&#39;s.</p><p> I purposefully tested the expensive Garmin Forerunner 745 first, so that I could start off with an understanding of the brand&#39;s more advanced tech. Testing the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATuucj1P-Eq1L8Yj1yxd5uxkLcWEewBLsK2jk1qvqCkG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGarmin-Forerunner-Running-Training-Support%2Fdp%2FB07Y62X3JS%3F">Forerunner 45S</a> , then, was an exercise in subtraction: If I pared down the feature set, would I miss the bells and whistles? And would other runners?</p><p> It turns out, mostly not. As an entry-level watch, the 45S offers everything beginners (and even some intermediate) runners could want, including distance tracking, basic fitness tracking (steps, calories), heart rate monitoring and a blood oxygen test. Also, as much as the 45S is aimed at new runners, you&#39;ll also find modes for indoor and outdoor cycling, elliptical machines, stair climbers and yoga.</p><p> Coming from the 745, I was especially pleased to see that many of Garmin&#39;s best training tools and recovery features carry down even to the base-level model. That includes training status, training load, training effect, Garmin Coach, Body Battery, stress tracking, a race time predictor and running dynamics analysis (again, an additional accessory is required). Like other Garmin watches, you can enable incident detection, with the caveat that you&#39;ll need your smartphone nearby for it to work.</p><p> It even functions as a perfunctory smartwatch, with smartphone notifications, music playback controls, calendar and weather widgets, and a duo of “find my phone” and “find my watch” features. Although I&#39;ve criticized Garmin&#39;s smartwatch features in the past for feeling like half-baked add-ons, I was still pleasantly surprised to find them on what&#39;s marketed as a running watch for novices.</p><p> As for the hardware, the watch feels lightweight, at 32 grams for the 39mm model (36g for the 42mm). It&#39;s available in five colors, slightly more than Garmin&#39;s more serious models. The 1.04-inch touchscreen was easy to glance at mid-workout, even in direct sunlight. The battery, which is rated for seven days (or 13 hours in GPS mode) does not need to be charged every day. In fact, if it really is beginners using this, their short trail runs should barely put a dent in the overall capacity. As with the Forerunner 745, my complaint is never with the impressive battery life, just the fact that you have to use a proprietary charging cable.</p><p> And, while this watch wasn&#39;t made for competitive swimmers, you can use it in the pool without breaking it. The 5 ATM water resistance rating means it can survive the equivalent of 50 meters of water pressure, which surely includes showering and shallow-water activities.</p><p> For what it&#39;s worth, there is a slightly more expensive model, the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDkyUkgyOEdOP3RoPTEmdGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8taWctMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjVkYWE1MDBjLTMxNDctM2RjOS04ZjVlLWQ1MDhmYTE0MDg3MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASBx4FMC_pYNLNlf4BAdS3zqBfkyXYSVlYsk31jmJlx2&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB092RH28GN%3Fth%3D1">Garmin Forerunner 55</a> , which adds respiration rate, menstrual tracking, an updated recovery time advisor and pacing strategies.</p><h2> The best under $100: Amazfit Bip S </h2><p><core-commerce id="20769e585274491aa7aca128216a410c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Lightweight design; long battery life; accurate GPS tracking; built-in heart rate monitor; water resistant; basic smartwatch features.</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Crude user interface; limited support for third-party apps; can&#39;t customize how workout stats are displayed on the screen; pausing workouts feels labored (which is a shame because you&#39;ll be doing it often).</p><p> I kept my expectations low when I began testing the <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazfit-bip-s-review-133036996.html">Bip S</a> . This <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3VzLmFtYXpmaXQuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2FtYXpmaXQtYmlwLXMiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjVkYWE1MDBjLTMxNDctM2RjOS04ZjVlLWQ1MDhmYTE0MDg3MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAU3DjrGdFyYRqdzEOGPiv-IXueovujyyToGvxGOgrfmd&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fus.amazfit.com%2Fproducts%2Famazfit-bip-s">$70 watch</a> comes from Amazfit, a lesser known brand here in the US that seems to specialize in lower-priced gadgets. Although I didn&#39;t know much about Amazfit or its parent company Huami, I was intrigued by the specs it offered at this price, most notably a built-in heart monitor — not something you typically see in a device this cheap.</p><p> As you might expect, a device this inexpensive has some trade-offs, and I&#39;ll get to those in a minute. But there&#39;s actually a lot to like. The watch itself is lightweight and water resistant, with a low-power color display that&#39;s easy to read in direct sunlight. That low-power design also means the battery lasts a long time — up to 40 hours on a charge. Perhaps most importantly, it excels in the area that matters most: as a sports watch. In my testing the built-in GPS allowed for accurate distance and pace tracking. If you&#39;re not a runner, or you just prefer a multi-sport life, the watch features nine other modes covering most common activities, including walking, yoga, cycling, pool and open-water swimming and free weights.</p><p> And did I mention the heart rate monitor? These readings are also seemingly accurate.</p><p> What you lose by settling for a watch this cheap is mainly the sort of polished user experience you&#39;d get with a device from a tier-one company like Apple or even Garmin (not that Garmin&#39;s app has ever been my favorite either). In my review, I noticed various goofs, including odd grammar and punctuation choices and a confusingly laid-out app.</p><p> I was also bummed to learn you could barely export your data to any third-party apps, other than Strava and Apple Health. You also can&#39;t customize the way data is displayed on-screen during a workout, while your goals don&#39;t auto-adjust the way they might on other platforms. Fortunately, at least, these are all issues that can be addressed after the fact via software updates — hopefully sooner rather than later.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-gps-running-watch-141513957.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-gps-running-watch-141513957.html?src=rss]]><source_id>engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5daa500c-3147-3dc9-8f5e-d508fa140873</guid><dc:creator> Dana Wollman</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jul 2023 11:38:34 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689680314</ingested><modified> 2023-07-18T11:38:48+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[polar]]></category><category><![CDATA[series4]]></category><category><![CDATA[news]]></category><category><![CDATA[applewatchseries6]]></category><category><![CDATA[engadgetoutdoors2019]]></category><category><![CDATA[health2019]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[wearables]]></category><category><![CDATA[commerce]]></category><category><![CDATA[garminforerunner645music]]></category><category><![CDATA[polarvantagem]]></category><category><![CDATA[running]]></category><category><![CDATA[apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[garmin]]></category><category><![CDATA[fitness]]></category><category><![CDATA[amazfitbips]]></category><category><![CDATA[gear]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicEquipment,Instruments&Components]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicsAccessories]]></category><category><![CDATA[OfficeElectronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology&Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Airline Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Dana Wollman]]></catego